  <record id="application.name=&quot;restrict.ess.profile&quot;" recordid="restrict.ess.profile">
    <application.name type="string">restrict.ess.profile</application.name>
    <appl.desc sctype="array">
      <appl.desc sctype="string">ffaegh(11/24/4004): Changed update in $G.sm.environment in start panel from false to ture to allow for updating fields in the form.</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">RAD Application Name: restrict.ess.profile</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">Description . . . . . . . . . : Restirct An ESS Operator's Service Desk And Incident Management Profiles</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">This application is executed when an ESS user logs in to ServiceCenter.</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">During the login process, the operator's Service Desk and Incident Management profiles are established based on the profiles entered on the operator record. The capabilities of these profiles are assumed to be that of a power user logging in.</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">However, if the operator logging in is an ESS user, the capabilities of these profiles are further restricted in this application.</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">Additionally, the following capability words are also stripped from the ESS user:</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">. SysAdmin</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">. SQLAdmin</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">The fact that these restrictions are being done from inside a RAD application IS BY DESIGN to make it very difficult for customers to circumvent these restrictions on an ESS user.</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">Parameters in to (I) or out from (O) this application are:</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">Parm             RAD                              Parm Name</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">Seq          Parm Type          I/O          (in this app)          Description</appl.desc>
      <appl.desc sctype="string"/>
      <appl.desc sctype="string">No parameters passed to or received from this application.</appl.desc>
    </appl.desc>
